sure if my charm offensive earned me an upgrade or whether the room I got was indeed the standard double I booked butif it was I am even more impressed. The room was a good size, spotlessly clean, nicely furnished. Very contemporary and modern. Good quality flat screen TV, beautiful bathroom with nice toiletries (The White Company if your interested!) Everything about it said quality, from the bed linen, the decor, the flooring, the soft fluffy white towels. And everything worked too! Safe, hairdryer, air-conditioningéˆ¥?Makes a nice change from some so-called 4* London hotels !! Surprisingly the air-conditioning worked even when the main power switch was off, which I realised when I mistakenly left it on one day. The housekeeping staff (who did a fantastic job by the way) even left it switched on which was nice of them - if not very environmentally friendly!The A/C unit was concealed as opposed to being fitted to the wall and was quiet and efficient. There was some road noise with the French door to the balcony open (I was in a room over-looking the Gran Via) but with the door shut the noise was virtually deadened. Iéˆ¥æª“ struggling to think of anything negative to say about the room and I think that says it alléˆ¥?if you have to look that hard for something negative then it is probably not worth mentioning.The location on the corner of Carrer de Casanova is good with plenty of shops, bars, restaurants, cash machines nearby. The Underground is about a 5 min walk away at Universitat and the start of Las Ramblaabout 5/10 mins further.All in all, Barcelona is a wonderful city and this is a fantastic hotel, and I will definitely be returning to both! 
