<Content>Modern, chic and central hotel I stayed here with two friends during the Easter holidays and had a great time. We chose a hotel at the last minute and the Casanova was perhaps a bit more than what we would have wanted to spend but I think we all felt that it was great and well worth it.The location is excellent - about 5 minutes from the Gaudi houses north of the Gran Via, 10 minutes from Plaza Catalunya, easy to get to the top of the Ramblas, the modern art museum, etc.The decor is very sleek and modern, with a green-lit reception area and lots of chocolate brown and swirly patterns in the rooms. The room we had was very spacious, with ample room for three beds, flat screen TV, nice big bathroom, good shower, etc etc. Despite being right in the city centre, it was reasonably quiet with the windows closed and curtains drawn.The breakfasts were superb - lots of meats, cheeses, toast, pastries, fruits, etc. The staff were generally friendly and helpful.The only minor annoyances were: (1) the shiny blankets are quite loud when they crinkle, so it's difficult to get to sleep and even harder to get back to sleep once you've woken up, and (2) for some reason, I couldn't quite figure out the A/C unit so I found it a bit hot at night.Other than that, it was all good - would happily stay here again. 
